gate: OPEN
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: S87 T3 — PolylineDecorator: fix arrow density regression at high zoom
requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
sprint: S87

context: |
  When zooming in on a track, direction arrows should appear more densely
  (more arrows visible in the viewport at the same physical spacing).
  Currently arrows become SPARSER at high zoom.

  Root cause: PolylineDecorator.tsx line 47:
    const spacing = Math.max(TARGET_SPACING_PX, totalLength / MAX_ARROWS_COUNT)
  `totalLength` is the full track length in pixel space, which grows as 2^zoom.
  At high zoom, spacing >> TARGET_SPACING_PX, causing sparse arrows even in
  the small visible viewport. The MAX_ARROWS_COUNT cap is there to avoid
  excessive DOM nodes when the full track is rendered.

  Fix strategy: compute spacing only over the VISIBLE viewport portion of
  the track, not the full track. This keeps density constant regardless of zoom
  while still preventing too many arrows from being placed in the current view.

steps:
  1. Open src/features/map/components/PolylineDecorator.tsx.
  2. Inside drawArrows(), after computing `points`, add a viewport filter:
       const bounds = map.getBounds()
       const visiblePoints = positions.filter(p =>
         bounds.contains(L.latLng(p[0], p[1]))
       )
     Use `visiblePoints` (or at minimum expand by 1 tile margin) to compute
     a `visibleLength` in pixel space the same way `totalLength` is computed.
  3. Replace the spacing formula:
       // OLD:
       const spacing = Math.max(TARGET_SPACING_PX, totalLength / MAX_ARROWS_COUNT)
       // NEW:
       const visibleLength = /* pixel length of track within visible bounds */
       const spacing = Math.max(TARGET_SPACING_PX, visibleLength / MAX_ARROWS_COUNT)
     Keep the full `points` array for actual arrow placement (not just visible),
     so arrows near viewport edges are also rendered. The spacing is now derived
     from the visible segment only.
  4. Verify: at zoom 10 arrows have natural density; zoom to 16 on a route
     segment — arrows appear denser (not sparser). No major lag on long tracks.

  Note: if the visible-segment approach introduces edge artifacts, an acceptable
  alternative is to drop the totalLength-based cap entirely and simply break
  when arrows.length >= MAX_ARROWS_COUNT (the loop already has this guard),
  letting TARGET_SPACING_PX drive density always. Confirm which produces
  better visual result before closing.

out:
  - src/features/map/components/PolylineDecorator.tsx

done:
  - Zooming in increases visible arrow count (denser spacing in viewport).
  - Zooming out does not produce 1000s of DOM nodes (MAX_ARROWS_COUNT respected).
  - Arrow redraw happens on zoomend (existing listener — no change needed).
  - TypeScript typecheck passes (pnpm tsc --noEmit).
